{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5f53cb22-9c2b-4f14-8e5b-8a7bcdc2ff9a","content":"Here are the **evaluation performance issues** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. File I/O Property Function (High Impact)\n**`EvalHeavy.csproj` line 13:**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nReading file contents during evaluation is expensive — it blocks the evaluation thread with synchronous I/O. This runs on *every* evaluation (IDE design-time builds, restores, etc.). **Fix:** Move file reading to a target with `Inputs/Outputs` so it only runs at build time.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Expensive Glob Pattern (Medium Impact)\n**`EvalHeavy.csproj` line 9:**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThis walks the entire directory tree during evaluation. If the directory contains `node_modules`, packages, or other large trees, this becomes very costly. **Fix:** Use `DefaultItemExcludes` to pre-exclude known heavy directories, or narrow the glob to specific extensions/subdirectories.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deep Import Chain (Low-Medium Impact)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nA 3-level deep chain (on top of the SDK's own imports). While manageable here, deep import chains increase evaluation time linearly. Each import requires file existence checks and XML parsing. Keep import depth minimal.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Issue | Location | Severity |\n|-------|----------|----------|\n| `File::ReadAllText` during eval | Line 13 | 🔴 High |\n| `**\\*.*` broad glob | Line 9 | 🟡 Medium |\n| Nested import chain (3 levels) | imports/ | 🟢 Low |\n\nThe highest-priority fix is removing the `ReadAllText` property function from evaluation-time and replacing the broad glob with a more targeted pattern.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9dad0aa5-f1ea-4c39-909d-a70fe9744059","outputTokens":489,"requestId":"F023:A7C8:134DB89:15D0489:69F94590"},"id":"15912c4e-27ad-4797-9fdd-8c5ba01b44dc","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:19:24.523Z","parentId":"46f02272-a56f-4a8c-9ea3-4c4543efe020"}
